<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Buffer-Overflow on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/buffer-overflow/</link><description>Recent content in Buffer-Overflow on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/buffer-overflow/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C Array Index Out of Bounds — Undefined Behavior Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/array-out-of-bounds/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/array-out-of-bounds/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-array-index-out-of-bounds--undefined-behavior-fix"&gt;[Solution] C Array Index Out of Bounds — Undefined Behavior Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;strong&gt;array index out of bounds&lt;/strong&gt; occurs when your program accesses an array element using an index that is less than zero or greater than or equal to the array&amp;rsquo;s size. In C, arrays have no built-in bounds checking — accessing an out-of-bounds element reads or writes whatever memory happens to be adjacent, causing undefined behavior, crashes, or silent data corruption.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C gets() Deprecated — Replace with fgets()</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/gets/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/gets/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-gets-deprecated--replace-with-fgets"&gt;[Solution] C gets() Deprecated — Replace with fgets()&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;gets()&lt;/code&gt; function was deprecated in C99 and removed in C11 because it is impossible to use safely. It reads input from stdin with no way to limit how many bytes are read into the buffer, making it the single most dangerous function in the C standard library. Every use of &lt;code&gt;gets()&lt;/code&gt; is a potential buffer overflow vulnerability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compiling with &lt;code&gt;-std=c11&lt;/code&gt; or newer:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Heap corruption detected</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/heap-corruption/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/heap-corruption/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="heap-corruption-detected"&gt;Heap corruption detected&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Heap corruption occurs when a program writes beyond the boundaries of heap-allocated memory, corrupting the heap metadata. The corruption is often detected later when &lt;code&gt;free()&lt;/code&gt; is called.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Buffer overflow on heap
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;buf &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strcpy&lt;/span&gt;(buf, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;this is a very long string&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// overflows
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Writing before allocated block
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;(p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// corrupts metadata
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Overlapping memcpy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;src &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;20&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;dst &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; src &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;memcpy&lt;/span&gt;(dst, src, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// overlapping
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-respect-buffer-boundaries"&gt;Fix 1: Respect buffer boundaries&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;buf &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strncpy&lt;/span&gt;(buf, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;short&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;9&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;buf[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;9&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;\0&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-dont-access-outside-allocated-block"&gt;Fix 2: Don&amp;rsquo;t access outside allocated block&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Only access p[0] through p[4]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-memmove-for-overlapping-regions"&gt;Fix 3: Use memmove for overlapping regions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;memmove&lt;/span&gt;(dst, src, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// handles overlap
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-valgrind-to-detect"&gt;Fix 4: Use Valgrind to detect&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;gcc -g -o prog prog.c
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;valgrind --tool&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;memcheck ./prog
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/double-free-heap/"&gt;Double free&lt;/a&gt; — heap metadata damage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/invalid-free/"&gt;Invalid free&lt;/a&gt; — invalid pointer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/use-after-free-heap/"&gt;Use after free&lt;/a&gt; — accessing freed memory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C scanf() Deprecated — Replace with fgets() + sscanf()</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/scanf/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/scanf/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-scanf-deprecated--replace-with-fgets--sscanf"&gt;[Solution] C scanf() Deprecated — Replace with fgets() + sscanf()&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;scanf()&lt;/code&gt; function family is deprecated in secure coding guidelines because &lt;code&gt;%s&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;%c&lt;/code&gt; specifiers read unbounded input, causing buffer overflows. While &lt;code&gt;scanf()&lt;/code&gt; itself is not removed from the standard, using it with string inputs is dangerous. The recommended pattern is to read a full line with &lt;code&gt;fgets()&lt;/code&gt; then parse with &lt;code&gt;sscanf()&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compiler warnings with security-hardened flags:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C sprintf() Deprecated — Replace with snprintf()</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/sprintf/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/sprintf/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-sprintf-deprecated--replace-with-snprintf"&gt;[Solution] C sprintf() Deprecated — Replace with snprintf()&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;sprintf()&lt;/code&gt; function is deprecated in modern C because it writes to a buffer without any bounds checking. If the formatted output exceeds the destination buffer size, it overflows into adjacent memory. The safe replacement is &lt;code&gt;snprintf()&lt;/code&gt;, which takes an explicit size parameter and truncates or returns the required length.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compiling with &lt;code&gt;_CRT_SECURE_NO_WARNINGS&lt;/code&gt; not defined on MSVC, or with security-focused compiler flags:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Stack smashing detected — buffer overflow</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/buffer-overflow-stack/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/buffer-overflow-stack/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stack-smashing-detected--buffer-overflow"&gt;Stack smashing detected — buffer overflow&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Stack smashing detected&amp;rdquo; occurs when a buffer overflow overwrites the stack canary (a guard value placed between local variables and the return address). The program aborts when it detects the canary has been corrupted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Writing past array bounds
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; buf[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strcpy&lt;/span&gt;(buf, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;this string is way too long&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// overflow
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Gets() with no bounds checking
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; buf[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;gets&lt;/span&gt;(buf); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// dangerous — no length limit
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Wrong buffer size in memcpy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; arr[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;memcpy&lt;/span&gt;(arr, large_data, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// overflow
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-bounds-checked-functions"&gt;Fix 1: Use bounds-checked functions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Instead of strcpy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strncpy&lt;/span&gt;(buf, src, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(buf) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;buf[&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(buf) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;\0&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Instead of gets
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fgets&lt;/span&gt;(buf, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(buf), stdin);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-validate-buffer-sizes"&gt;Fix 2: Validate buffer sizes&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;copy_string&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;dest, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;size_t&lt;/span&gt; dest_size, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;src) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (dest_size &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;size_t&lt;/span&gt; i;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; dest_size &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; src[i] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;\0&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;; i&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;++&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; dest[i] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; src[i];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; dest[i] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;\0&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-compile-with-stack-protection"&gt;Fix 3: Compile with stack protection&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;gcc -fstack-protector-strong -o prog prog.c
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;string.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; buf[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;20&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Safe: use fgets
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Enter name: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fgets&lt;/span&gt;(buf, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(buf), stdin);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Remove trailing newline
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; buf[&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strcspn&lt;/span&gt;(buf, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;\0&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, %s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, buf);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/buffer-overflow-stack/"&gt;Buffer overflow on stack&lt;/a&gt; — stack overflow details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/use-after-free-heap/"&gt;Use after free&lt;/a&gt; — heap memory error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/segmentation-fault-0/"&gt;Segfault at 0x0&lt;/a&gt; — null pointer crash.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Stack Smashing Detected — Buffer Overflow Security Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/buffer-overflow/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/buffer-overflow/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stack-smashing-detected--buffer-overflow-security-fix"&gt;[Solution] C Stack Smashing Detected — Buffer Overflow Security Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;* stack smashing detected *&lt;strong&gt;: terminated&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is printed by glibc when a stack-based buffer overflow overwrites the stack canary — a secret value placed on the stack by the compiler to detect buffer overflows. When &lt;code&gt;main()&lt;/code&gt; or a function returns, the runtime checks the canary; if it was modified, the program is killed immediately to prevent potential exploitation. This is a security-critical error that must be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C strcat() Deprecated — Replace with strlcat() or snprintf()</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/strcat/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/strcat/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-strcat-deprecated--replace-with-strlcat-or-snprintf"&gt;[Solution] C strcat() Deprecated — Replace with strlcat() or snprintf()&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;strcat()&lt;/code&gt; function is deprecated in secure coding guidelines because it appends to a destination buffer without any bounds checking. If the combined length of the destination and source exceeds the buffer, it causes a buffer overflow. The safe replacements are &lt;code&gt;strlcat()&lt;/code&gt; (BSD/glibc) or using &lt;code&gt;snprintf()&lt;/code&gt; to build the string.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compiler warnings with security-hardened build flags:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;warning: &amp;#39;strcat&amp;#39; is deprecated: use strlcat() or snprintf() instead
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;On MSVC:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C strcpy() Deprecated — Replace with strncpy() or strlcpy()</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/strcpy/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/strcpy/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-strcpy-deprecated--replace-with-strncpy-or-strlcpy"&gt;[Solution] C strcpy() Deprecated — Replace with strncpy() or strlcpy()&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;strcpy()&lt;/code&gt; function is deprecated in secure coding guidelines because it copies a string to a destination buffer without any bounds checking. If the source string is longer than the destination buffer, it causes a buffer overflow. The safe replacements are &lt;code&gt;strncpy()&lt;/code&gt; (C standard) or &lt;code&gt;strlcpy()&lt;/code&gt; (BSD/glibc, preferred).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compiler warnings with security flags:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;warning: &amp;#39;strcpy&amp;#39; is deprecated: use strncpy() or strlcpy() instead
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;On MSVC:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Runtime Error 0xC0000409 Stack Buffer Overflow Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/runtime-error-c0000409/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/runtime-error-c0000409/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-runtime-error-0xc0000409-stack-buffer-overflow-fix"&gt;[Solution] Runtime Error 0xC0000409 Stack Buffer Overflow Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Runtime error 0xC00000409 is a Stack Buffer Overflow error that occurs when a program writes more data to a stack-based buffer than it was allocated. Windows terminates the process immediately as a security measure — stack buffer overflows can be exploited for code execution attacks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error affects both Windows 10 and 11 and maps to &lt;code&gt;STATUS_STACK_BUFFER_OVERRUN&lt;/code&gt;. Unlike many other runtime errors, this one is often caused by bugs in application code rather than system issues, but it can also indicate malware or security exploits.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>